# Testing Conventions

## Pyramid

| Layer       | Ratio | Stack                                            |
|-------------|-------|--------------------------------------------------|
| Unit        | ~70%  | xUnit + FluentAssertions + NSubstitute           |
| Integration | ~25%  | + Testcontainers Postgres + Respawn              |
| E2E         | ~5%   | + WebApplicationFactory                          |

## Test naming convention

`{Method}_{Scenario}_{ExpectedResult}_{BR_ID}`

```csharp
[Fact]
public async Task SubmitReport_NoPhoto_ReturnsValidationError_BR_REP_001() { ... }

[Fact]
public void Verify_FromSubmitted_RaisesReportVerifiedEvent_BR_REP_020() { ... }
```

## Hard rules

- AAA (Arrange-Act-Assert), no shared state via static fields.
- **NEVER mock `DbContext`** — use Testcontainers Postgres.
- Mock ONLY boundaries: S3, AI, email, FCM, SMS gateway.
- Respawn for schema reset between test classes (NOT full DB drop).
- Every BR listed in a handler MUST have ≥ 1 test.
- Happy path + ≥ 1 error case per endpoint.

## Integration test scaffold

```csharp
public sealed class ReportQueryTests : IAsyncLifetime
{
    private readonly PostgreSqlContainer _postgres = new PostgreSqlBuilder()
        .WithImage("postgis/postgis:18-3.4")
        .Build();

    public async Task InitializeAsync()
    {
        await _postgres.StartAsync();
        // build DbContext, apply migrations
    }

    public async Task DisposeAsync() => await _postgres.DisposeAsync();
}
```

## Run tests

```powershell
dotnet test                                              # all
dotnet test tests/Greenlens.Domain.UnitTests/            # one project
dotnet test --filter "FullyQualifiedName~BR_REP_001"     # by BR ID
dotnet test --collect:"XPlat Code Coverage"              # coverage
```

## Failure triage

When a test fails, classify:
- **Code Bug** — fix the production code.
- **Test Bug** — fix the test only after confirming production code is correct.
- **Environment** — Testcontainers / Docker / network — fix infra, not code.
- **Flaky** — async race, time-dependence, ordering — add `[Retry]` only after root cause analysis.

Always reference the related BR in the fix commit.
